message: VIT is an amazing place if you want to pursue engineering in India. It has the advantage of Fully Flexible Credit System (FFCS) where you get to chose your class timings & faculty. You can easily clear the exams if you attend classes regularly and put little efforts before the exam. Lot of student clubs, chapters, 1 four day cultural fest (Riviera) and 1 three day knowledge fest (graVITas). You'll also love the hostel life here and food is good as well if you choose the speci...al mess. Knowledgeable faculty who are always there if you need any assistance. All in all, one of the better engineering colleges in India - not too much of academic strain and you'll definitely get a good placement with some sincere efforts. If you're planning for higher studies you have in campus coaching for all competitive entrances as well. Batch of 2013-2017 VIT University, Vellore Campus Mechanical ( Spec. message: Seriously! What the hell is wrong with this college? 10k STUDENTS got admission this year(2017). Have they gone mad? The whole campus is completely crowded. You can't walk without bumping into someone. Being a student in VIT, I've realized that VIT is all about outer beauty just to attract more students into joining the college. And the worst part is they keep admitting more and more students every year. They have spent crores of rupees, just to rebuild the existing main gate.... Instead they could have built the tunnels properly which we students use every single day to go to our class. The tunnel is filled with drainage water and we have to walk through it. For students having classes at 8 o'clock, the tunnel gets so crowded that it takes nearly 10 mins just to pass through it. VIT keeps increasing the number of students but not the facilities inside the college for the students. Currently, there are nearly 30k students in VIT and 10 shuttle cabs. Each shuttle cab can accommodate at most 10 people. So during rainy days, only 300 students would be able to use the cab(considering the cab drivers can make 3 trips during the busy hours) . The other 29700 students will have to walk through the same old stinky tunnel whose condition has now worsened because of the rain. See more

message: Wonderful University..!! For all the people who want enough freedom to discover new things and flourish in their place of interests, LPU is a wonderful place..!!  Coming to the Faculty, you confront wonderful and highly qualified faculty.. There are some exceptions though..some of the Faculty might be qualified but they aren't worth their qualification.. But remember every University does have some exceptions.. Studies and Practicals are not to be worried about. The curriculu...m is according to renowned  universities like Harvard and MIT. Practicals are conducted well by a good Lab assistant and Lecturer.  Coming to Living Conditions, the Hostels are well built with good infrastructure. Students can opt their own type of Room. Dorms are also available. The food provided in the mess might not be suitable for most of the students, but its not a matter of concern as there are many Stalls and Food Kiosks that are reliable. Good living conditions after all. Coming to Entertainment, LPU provides with wonderful sports grounds for different sports like Cricket, Athletics, Football, Table - Tennis, KhoKho, and many more. Different types of cultural activities and programmes are conducted frequently, and active participation of students is observed. If students are doing well in a particular field, he is given support. Therefore, Entertainment is given importance too.. Well.. These may be helpful to many people who want to take admissions in Lovely Professional University... I'm sorry if I had offended anyone.. Thank you.. See more

message: Lovely Professional University (LPU) is a private semi-residential university in North India created under the Punjab State Private University Act 2005 and recognized by UGC[6] under Section 2(f) of UGC Act 1956. LPU offers a wide spectrum of more than 200 programmes and courses at diploma, under-graduate, graduate, post graduate, and doctoral levels. With its state-of -the-art high-tech infrastructure, benchmarked pedagogy, research oriented faculty, interdisciplinary resear...ch initiatives, student centric approach, and international tie-ups of repute, the university has more than 25,000 students from 29 states and 28 countries around the world. Situated on the National Highway-1, at the entry of Jalandhar City, on a 600+ acre serene environ, the university offers a wide range of residential facilities for more than 18,000 students, separately for boys and girls. LPU has connections with more than 50+ universities and institutes worldwide in USA, UK, Australia, Canada, Singapore, Brazil, Poland, and Ghana for twinning programmes and student exchanges See more
